Description: Corroded copper alloy large leaf-shaped arrow-head, with rounded tip and a mid-rib on both sides ending with a conical socket.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 77 § 76, pl. xxxix, 10)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.71, p.183, pl.25)
